document.full_text: a five-mile stretch of the mississippi river was closed to commercial traffic near baton rouge, louisiana, on friday after a barge struck a dock and three grain barges in tow sank, the u.s. coast guard said.
document.title: river traffic, people and animals feel strain of flooding
